story.intro.fox.0.0.40: Long ago, there was a player named Stevo.
story.intro.fox.0.2.40: However, he grew bored of this challenge.
story.intro.fox.0.3.37: He ran a command he didn't understand.
story.intro.fox.0.4.51: Giving all mobs the ability to think for themselves.
story.intro.fox.0.8.29: He wanted to battle every mob.
story.intro.fox.0.9.42: But a little fox proved to be more cunning.
story.intro.fox.0.10.33: And defeated the player in battle.
story.intro.fox.0.11.57: The player was impressed, and became friends with the fox.
story.intro.fox.0.12.35: Together the two explored the world.
story.intro.fox.0.13.52: They built many structures, and befriended many mobs.
story.intro.fox.0.14.65: The player anointed the fox as king when the player wasn't around.
story.intro.fox.0.17.31: Forever leaving the fox as king.
story.outro.bad.fox.0.0.35: The fox had victory over the evoker.
story.outro.bad.fox.0.1.42: The fox tried to banish the evoker forever.
story.outro.bad.fox.0.2.39: But the evoker's powers were too strong.
story.outro.bad.fox.0.3.38: The evoker returned to his former reign
story.outro.good.fox.0.1.36: With the power from all the diamonds,
story.outro.good.fox.0.2.34: the evoker was banished to the end.
story.outro.good.fox.0.4.38: There was once again peace in the land.
story.outro.good.fox.0.5.40: The player returned, watching from above.
story.outro.good.fox.0.6.42: Amazed again at the little fox's victories.
story.outro.good.fox.0.7.46: The player spoke for the first time in a while:
story.outro.greedy.fox.0.0.30: The evoker had trapped the fox.
story.outro.greedy.fox.0.3.31: And he escaped, ready to return.
